        WEB_SITE="http://solvespace.com/"
      LICENSE[0]="GPL"
         ENTERED=20160613
        KEYWORDS=""
           SHORT="a parametric 2d/3d CAD"
cat << EOF
SOLVESPACE is a parametric 3d CAD program. Applications include:

* modeling 3d parts — draw with extrudes, revolves, and Boolean
  (union / difference) operations
* modeling 2d parts — draw the part as a single section, and export DXF, PDF,
  SVG; use 3d assembly to verify fit
* 3d-printed parts — export the STL or other triangle mesh expected by
most 3d
  printers
* preparing CAM data — export 2d vector art for a waterjet machine or laser
  cutter; or generate STEP or STL, for import into third-party CAM software
  for machining
* mechanism design — use the constraint solver to simulate planar or spatial
  linkages, with pin, ball, or slide joints
* plane and solid geometry — replace hand-solved trigonometry and
spreadsheets
  with a live dimensioned drawing
EOF
